---
/**
 * HomeHero — the commercial lead that sits above the posts index.
 *
 * Three beats, in the order a stranger needs them: what I do, who it's for,
 * what changes. Primary CTA routes to /services (the qualify-as-much-as-attract
 * page); email is the conversion there. Kept compact on purpose — this is a
 * blog first, so the hero states the offer and gets out of the way.
 *
 * Self-contained markup + scoped layout styles; the filled button is the
 * shared global `.cta-btn` (pages.css) so the hero and /services never drift.
 * Dual-mode via .eng-only / .paper-only chrome; the statement itself is the
 * page <h1>, which is why index.astro demotes "./posts" to an <h2>.
 */
---
<section class="home-hero" aria-label="What I do">
  <p class="hh-eyebrow">
    <span class="eng-only">&gt; whoami --short</span>
    <span class="paper-only">Jonathan Abraham — AI systems engineer</span>
  </p>

  <h1 class="hh-statement">
    I build production-grade AI systems — voice agents, intake automation, and
    the backend they run on.
  </h1>

  <p class="hh-sub">
    For teams whose AI prototype works in a demo but isn't a product yet. I take
    it from a messy idea to a system that survives real users, real volume, and
    real regulation.
  </p>

  <div class="hh-actions">
    <a class="cta-btn" href="/services">
      <span class="eng-only">▸ what i can help with</span>
      <span class="paper-only">What I can help with →</span>
    </a>
    <a class="cta-btn ghost" href="/about">
      <span class="eng-only">./about</span>
      <span class="paper-only">More about me</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Top padding clears the fixed nav (matches the page-head it replaces as
     the first element); bottom hairline divides the offer from the blog. */
  .home-hero {
    padding: 78px 0 30px;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .hh-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: .06em;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  /* Statement stays mono in both modes — mirrors FeaturedPosts' feature-title,
     the established "editorial heading" treatment in paper mode. */
  .hh-statement {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(23px, 3.2vw, 36px);
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    max-width: 30ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .hh-sub {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    max-width: 62ch;
    margin: 0 0 26px;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .hh-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px 16px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .home-hero { padding: 56px 0 24px; }
    .hh-sub { font-size: 15px; }
  }
</style>
